<fig id="Fig3"><label>Fig. 3</label><caption><p>A flow diagram of three coefficient of determination (CD) statistics. The group average CD (CD<sub>_</sub>GrpAve) is shown in A. A1: A relationship matrix of seven individuals. A2: Calculate the mean relationships within and between units. A3: Group average CD is calculated by scaling group average PEVD (PEVD<sub>_</sub>GrpAve) by the quantity obtained from the PEVD equation using the within and between unit means. The individual average CD (CD<sub>_</sub>IdAve) is shown in B. B1: A relationship matrix of seven individuals. B2: Calculate pairwise relationship differences of individuals between the units. Subscripts <italic>i</italic> and <italic>j</italic> refer to the <italic>i</italic>th and <italic>j</italic>th individuals in units 1 and 2, respectively. B3: Individual average CD is calculated by scaling indvidual average PEVD (PEVD<sub>_</sub>IdAve) with the average of pairwise relationship differences of individuals. The CD of contrast (CD<sub>_</sub>Contrast) is shown in C. CD<sub>_</sub>Contrast is calculated by scaling the prediction error variance of the differences (PEVD) of contrast with the product of the transpose of the contrast vector (<bold>x</bold>), the relationship matrix (<bold>K</bold>), and the contrast vector</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="12864_2021_7414_Fig3_HTML" id="MO3"/></fig></p>
